he says you're the best,

1458
01:19:27,704 --> 01:19:28,912
and the best is
what I need right now.

1459
01:19:28,997 --> 01:19:31,249
HELLER: (ON PHONE)
We froze our butts
together in Korea.

1460
01:19:31,333 --> 01:19:32,667
How can I help you,
Sam?

1461
01:19:32,751 --> 01:19:35,503
Well, it's a simple petition
for a restraining order,

1462
01:19:35,587 --> 01:19:37,380
but there's been
some complications.

1463
01:19:37,464 --> 01:19:38,841
Now,
I know this is
short notice,

1464
01:19:38,925 --> 01:19:40,843
but look,
I need this injunction.

1465
01:19:40,927 --> 01:19:43,512
You see,
there's an ex-convict
by the name of Max Cady,

1466
01:19:43,596 --> 01:19:44,638
he's been
harassing my family.

1467
01:19:44,723 --> 01:19:48,268
I'm sorry, Mr. Bowden.
I can't continue
this conversation.

1468
01:19:48,352 --> 01:19:50,061
Well, is there
a more convenient time?

1469
01:19:50,146 --> 01:19:52,731
No, no. The damn thing
is I have a conflict.

1470
01:19:52,815 --> 01:19:54,608
Now, what would
that be?
Well, you see,

1471
01:19:54,693 --> 01:19:57,528
Mr. Cady retained
my services
as of yesterday.

1472
01:19:57,612 --> 01:19:58,654
He what?

1473
01:19:58,739 --> 01:20:00,657
In fact,
I see on my phone sheet

1474
01:20:00,742 --> 01:20:02,284
Mr. Cady called
this morning,

1475
01:20:02,368 --> 01:20:03,452
so I'm sure
he'll fill me in...

1476
01:20:03,536 --> 01:20:07,164
But wait a minute, Lee.
Now, look, this man
is a psychotic.

1477
01:20:07,248 --> 01:20:10,793
It appears
I'll be seeing you at
that hearing after all.

1478
01:20:12,588 --> 01:20:13,796
CADY ON TAPE:
Could you repeat that?

1479
01:20:13,881 --> 01:20:16,050
SAM ON TAPE: I said
if you don't leave...

1480
01:20:17,052 --> 01:20:18,886
If you don't
leave my family alone

1481
01:20:18,970 --> 01:20:21,138
and if you don't
get out of here,

1482
01:20:21,222 --> 01:20:24,309
you're gonna be hurting
like you never dreamed.

1483
01:20:25,311 --> 01:20:26,269
A threat?

1484
01:20:26,353 --> 01:20:28,772
Yeah, you bet your ass
that's a threat.

1485
01:20:29,983 --> 01:20:34,070
HELLER:
You need only glance
at my client to know

1486
01:20:34,905 --> 01:20:37,115
that Mr. Bowden
made good

1487
01:20:37,200 --> 01:20:40,535
on his heinous
and cowardly threat.

1488
01:20:41,079 --> 01:20:43,413
Just as God arose
to judgment

1489
01:20:43,498 --> 01:20:45,291
to save all the meek
of the earth,

1490
01:20:45,375 --> 01:20:48,294
I hope and pray
you will do
the same, sir.

1491
01:20:48,378 --> 01:20:49,962
Your Honor,
(CLEARS THROAT)

1492
01:20:50,714 --> 01:20:53,926
Mr. Cady wouldn't
have surreptitiously
taped our meeting

1493
01:20:54,010 --> 01:20:56,136
unless he knew
that he'd...

1494
01:20:57,806 --> 01:21:01,684
This court
does not condone

1495
01:21:02,645 --> 01:21:06,690
feuds, vendettas
or vigilantism.

1496
01:21:07,275 --> 01:21:12,071
Let me quote our
great Negro educator,
Mr. Booker T. Washington.

1497
01:21:12,865 --> 01:21:17,119
"I will let no man
drag me down so low

1498
01:21:18,287 --> 01:21:20,706
"as to make me
hate him."

1499
01:21:20,791 --> 01:21:21,874
Yes.

1500
01:21:22,709 --> 01:21:25,378
I will grant
the restraining order

1501
01:21:25,462 --> 01:21:28,966
not to validate
the malice between you,

1502
01:21:29,050 --> 01:21:34,138
but in the interest
of Christian harmony.

1503
01:21:35,724 --> 01:21:38,810
You may not come
within 500 yards

1504
01:21:38,894 --> 01:21:43,482
of Mr. Maximilian Cady

1505
01:21:44,234 --> 01:21:48,989
until such time
as the court may
lift the injunction.

1506
01:21:50,616 --> 01:21:54,578
King Solomon could
not have adjudicated
more wisely, Your Honor.

1507
01:21:55,371 --> 01:22:00,042
I am so offended by
the philistine tactics
of Mr. Bowden,

1508
01:22:00,127 --> 01:22:04,339
I petitioned the A. B.A.
For his disbarment

1509
01:22:04,424 --> 01:22:06,842
on the grounds of
moral turpitude.

1510
01:22:07,177 --> 01:22:10,179
Now, if you will
excuse us, my client...

1511
01:22:10,263 --> 01:22:11,264
Come on, son...

1512
01:22:11,390 --> 01:22:13,099
Is due back
at the hospital

1513
01:22:15,728 --> 01:22:20,149
for the results of
his numerous X-rays.

1514
01:22:22,736 --> 01:22:23,861
Kersek, I want a gun.

1515
01:22:24,321 --> 01:22:25,530
I need a gun.
I want a gun.

1516
01:22:25,615 --> 01:22:26,781
You want a gun?

1517
01:22:26,866 --> 01:22:27,949
Yeah, I need a gun.

1518
01:22:28,618 --> 01:22:29,701
Know anything
about guns?
No.

1519
01:22:29,785 --> 01:22:30,869
No, I don't believe
in them.

1520
01:22:30,953 --> 01:22:32,413
I never had them
around the house
or anything.

1521
01:22:32,497 --> 01:22:33,539
All right,
I'll get you a gun.

1522
01:22:33,624 --> 01:22:35,041
What kind of
gun you want?
Now, calm down.

1523
01:22:35,125 --> 01:22:37,126
Well, just something simple,
something I can handle.

1524
01:22:37,211 --> 01:22:40,214
Let me see
what fits you. A.45...

1525
01:22:40,298 --> 01:22:41,590
Let me see your hands.
Okay.

1526
01:22:43,468 --> 01:22:45,719
A.38 snub-nosed
special. Yeah.
All right. Good.

1527
01:22:45,803 --> 01:22:48,056
That'll do. I can even
teach you how to use it.

1528
01:22:48,140 --> 01:22:50,016
All right. Great.
The first lesson
is this.

1529
01:22:50,517 --> 01:22:52,894
Don't think of it
as shooting a man
or trying to kill him.

1530
01:22:53,020 --> 01:22:55,064
Right.
Think of it as
an extension of your fist.

1531
01:22:55,148 --> 01:22:57,149
You're just reaching out
and knocking the man down.

1532
01:22:57,817 --> 01:22:58,817
All right.

1533
01:22:58,902 --> 01:23:01,028
Later on we can
go out to the woods
and shoot some trees, okay?

1534
01:23:01,113 --> 01:23:03,782
That'd be great.
That'd be great. Good.

1535
01:23:05,910 --> 01:23:07,661
What is it? What?

1536
01:23:07,745 --> 01:23:09,580
Well, Sam...
Yeah?

1537
01:23:09,665 --> 01:23:12,124
I give you a gun.
You pull it on Cady,

1538
01:23:12,209 --> 01:23:13,251
and it's gonna
dawn on you

1539
01:23:13,335 --> 01:23:14,335
that shooting a man
is different

1540
01:23:14,419 --> 01:23:16,213
than blowing holes
in some tree.

1541
01:23:16,297 --> 01:23:18,507
Next thing, you know,
you don't have my gun,
Cady does.

1542
01:23:19,008 --> 01:23:20,050
No, no, no.
You're gonna teach me.

1543
01:23:20,134 --> 01:23:21,551
I know how
to handle a gun.

1544
01:23:21,636 --> 01:23:22,762
He won't take it
away from me.

1545
01:23:22,846 --> 01:23:25,807
Best-case scenario,
you kill Cady dog-dead.

1546
01:23:26,809 --> 01:23:30,187
Fifteen years to life.
Do you realize that,
Counselor?

1547
01:23:35,986 --> 01:23:38,863
Oh, Jesus!
It's all fucked up,
Kersek!

1548
01:23:39,740 --> 01:23:40,991
I mean,
the law considers me

1549
01:23:41,075 --> 01:23:42,909
more of a loose cannon
than Max Cady!

1550
01:23:42,994 --> 01:23:45,288
Some big-shit attorney
has whipped

1551
01:23:45,372 --> 01:23:47,623
the A. B.A.'s
ethics committee
into a frenzy.

1552
01:23:48,125 --> 01:23:50,960
There's an emergency session
in Raleigh over the assault.

1553
01:23:51,336 --> 01:23:53,046
How did they link that
to you?

1554
01:23:53,214 --> 01:23:57,342
I went to warn Cady.
I thought it was
the decent thing to do.

1555
01:23:57,427 --> 01:24:00,388
Maybe I'd scare him.
And he was wired.

1556
01:24:03,142 --> 01:24:04,976
Goddamn fools.

1557
01:24:08,440 --> 01:24:10,316
This hearing,
it's real important?

1558
01:24:10,400 --> 01:24:11,900
(LAUGHS)

1559
01:24:12,569 --> 01:24:16,072
Only if I want to continue
to practice law. Yeah.

1560
01:24:17,199 --> 01:24:18,241
Cady isn't
expected there, is he?

1561
01:24:18,743 --> 01:24:22,038
Oh, no, no, no.
Mr. Cady,
he's beyond reproach.

1562
01:24:22,164 --> 01:24:23,831
But you're required
to be there.
Yeah.

1563
01:24:25,125 --> 01:24:26,167
When is this hearing?

1564
01:24:26,251 --> 01:24:28,337
It's Thursday morning,
9:00.

1565
01:24:28,421 --> 01:24:31,173
The torture begins
and lasts for two days.

1566
01:24:32,383 --> 01:24:33,675
You have to fly up
the night before?

1567
01:24:34,635 --> 01:24:35,803
Right.

1568
01:24:36,722 --> 01:24:38,514
Cady's an opportunist.

1569
01:24:38,599 --> 01:24:40,558
If he thinks
you're gonna be out
of town for two days,

1570
01:24:40,642 --> 01:24:43,354
that's going to be
as tempting to him
as shit is to a fly.

1571
01:24:44,105 --> 01:24:45,689
If Cady breaks
into your home,

1572
01:24:45,774 --> 01:24:47,483
he can be killed.

1573
01:24:47,567 --> 01:24:48,942
Justifiably.

1574
01:24:50,988 --> 01:24:53,740
But he won't show
unless he's real sure
you're not gonna be there.

1575
01:25:31,826 --> 01:25:33,160
(SWITCHING STATIONS)

1576
01:25:34,830 --> 01:25:36,789
(CHOIR SINGING)

1577
01:26:02,987 --> 01:26:03,987
Have a good trip.

1578
01:26:04,071 --> 01:26:05,780
All right. Bye-bye.

1579
01:26:05,865 --> 01:26:06,865
Call us tonight, okay?

1580
01:26:06,949 --> 01:26:08,283
All right.

1581
01:26:18,713 --> 01:26:20,297
I didn't miss
the 9:20 to Raleigh?

1582
01:26:20,381 --> 01:26:22,674
I'm afraid you did, sir.
But there's a 10:20.

1583
01:26:22,758 --> 01:26:23,843
Oh, it's not that.

1584
01:26:23,927 --> 01:26:26,888
I just have some very,
very important papers
for Samuel Bowden.

1585
01:26:27,389 --> 01:26:28,639
Was he on the 9:20?

1586
01:26:29,558 --> 01:26:31,268
We can't give out
that information, sir.

1587
01:26:32,061 --> 01:26:33,562
Well, it's just...

1588
01:26:34,355 --> 01:26:36,231
I guess I could send it
to him overnight,

1589
01:26:36,316 --> 01:26:40,069
but he might be back,
for all I know,
tomorrow morning, and I...

1590
01:26:41,405 --> 01:26:42,739
See, I...

1591
01:26:43,115 --> 01:26:46,410
My wife and I have
been in an accident,
and he's our lawyer.

1592
01:26:46,495 --> 01:26:50,664
And if I don't get
in touch with him,
we could lose this case.

1593
01:26:50,749 --> 01:26:53,668
We've already lost
our little daughter, Dani.

1594
01:26:54,921 --> 01:26:56,046
Is...

1595
01:26:57,757 --> 01:26:58,924
Is there any way
I can find out

1596
01:26:59,008 --> 01:27:01,719
if he was on that flight
and when he's coming back?

1597
01:27:01,803 --> 01:27:03,930
It'd really,
really help us.

1598
01:27:06,517 --> 01:27:07,601
(KEYS CLATTERING)

1599
01:27:14,067 --> 01:27:16,027
He'll be back the day
after tomorrow, sir.

1600
01:27:16,779 --> 01:27:18,404
Bless your heart.

1601
01:27:33,631 --> 01:27:35,215
(SOFTLY)
Go on. Go on in.

1602
01:27:37,970 --> 01:27:39,470
Get down, Sam.

1603
01:27:44,852 --> 01:27:47,104
(BANGING ON DOOR)
Leigh. Leigh,
give me a cigarette.

1604
01:27:48,481 --> 01:27:49,648
You better
slow down, Sam.

1605
01:27:49,732 --> 01:27:51,693
You're outpacing me
two-to-one since
you started smoking.

1606
01:27:51,777 --> 01:27:54,404
Just keep track of
how many I owe you.

1607
01:27:56,323 --> 01:27:57,448
So, how'd it go
at the airport?

1608
01:27:57,533 --> 01:27:58,742
Well, we did our thing,

1609
01:27:58,827 --> 01:28:00,160
but we don't know
if he saw us,

1610
01:28:00,245 --> 01:28:02,288
we don't even know
if he was there.

1611
01:28:02,789 --> 01:28:04,832
Set the trap
and we'll see.

1612
01:28:05,376 --> 01:28:06,543
What if we don't
want to see?

1613
01:28:06,919 --> 01:28:08,295
Dani!
DANIELLE: What?

1614
01:28:08,588 --> 01:28:10,463
Maybe he
poisoned the dog.

1615
01:28:10,798 --> 01:28:12,758
Dani...
Sam, watch out
for the windows.

1616
01:28:12,843 --> 01:28:15,845
Yeah, you're not
allowed to stand up,
Dad, remember?

1617
01:28:22,437 --> 01:28:23,604
Didn't Cady
go after her?

1618
01:28:23,688 --> 01:28:24,855
LEIGH:
You don't know Dani.

1619
01:28:24,939 --> 01:28:26,941
If she finds
a palmetto bug
in her bedroom,

1620
01:28:27,026 --> 01:28:28,776
she takes it outside.

1621
01:28:28,861 --> 01:28:31,237
You know, she could
never kill anything.

1622
01:28:31,322 --> 01:28:32,780
Even a six-foot
palmetto bug?

1623
01:28:32,865 --> 01:28:34,199
(LAUGHS)

1624
01:28:35,702 --> 01:28:37,202
Oh, God.

1625
01:28:46,005 --> 01:28:47,047
What is that?

1626
01:28:48,299 --> 01:28:51,761
It's a monofilament line.
I got it from
Sam's fishing gear.

1627
01:28:51,845 --> 01:28:54,513
See, what I do is
I stretch it across
the windows and the doors

1628
01:28:54,598 --> 01:28:56,600
and tie it to
Dani's teddy bear here.

1629
01:28:56,684 --> 01:28:58,268
If the bear moves
a quarter of an inch,

1630
01:28:58,353 --> 01:28:59,895
I'll know
if the holy ghost
is sneaking in.

1631
01:29:32,100 --> 01:29:33,892
What are you reading?

1632
01:29:37,980 --> 01:29:39,148
Why? Did Kersek quit?

1633
01:29:39,233 --> 01:29:40,316
No.

1634
01:29:41,360 --> 01:29:43,194
It's just
that Cady said...

1635
01:29:43,278 --> 01:29:45,113
You want some answers.

1636
01:29:46,616 --> 01:29:47,825
Me, too.

1637
01:29:50,120 --> 01:29:54,999
I'd like to know just
how strong we are
or how weak.

1638
01:29:57,628 --> 01:29:59,421
But I guess
the only way we're going
to find that out

1639
01:29:59,505 --> 01:30:02,675
is just by
going through this.

1640
01:30:06,513 --> 01:30:10,308
It's just that Cady said
to read the book between
Esther and Psalms.

1641
01:30:11,227 --> 01:30:12,853
Which is which one?

1642
01:30:13,354 --> 01:30:14,980
The Book of Job.

1643
01:30:18,152 --> 01:30:20,987
Job was a good man.
He believed in God

1644
01:30:22,114 --> 01:30:24,116
and God tested
his faith.

1645
01:30:24,534 --> 01:30:26,827
He took away
everything he had,

1646
01:30:28,455 --> 01:30:30,206
even his children.

1647
01:30:34,003 --> 01:30:35,295
(GASPS)

1648
01:30:46,517 --> 01:30:49,436
DANIELLE:
It's hideous, this plan.
I mean, barbaric.

1649
01:30:49,520 --> 01:30:53,024
They're crazy.
My dad's turned
into some kind of...

1650
01:30:53,108 --> 01:30:54,275
I don't know what.

1651
01:30:54,359 --> 01:30:55,651
Barbaric.

1652
01:30:55,736 --> 01:30:57,612
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1653
01:30:59,032 --> 01:31:03,285
Listen to your father.
Do what they say.
What else you can do?

1654
01:31:03,369 --> 01:31:06,331
Leave. We could go
to the houseboat,
you know,

1655
01:31:06,415 --> 01:31:08,458
and get lost
in any inlet.

1656
01:31:13,215 --> 01:31:14,715
Dani, come on.

1657
01:31:15,217 --> 01:31:16,926
Don't stay outside.

1658
01:31:23,643 --> 01:31:28,064
You wanna know what
really disturbs me?
It's killing this guy.

1659
01:31:29,358 --> 01:31:31,526
I mean,
taking a man's life.

1660
01:31:33,445 --> 01:31:36,073
I don't know if
I can live with that.

1661
01:31:36,324 --> 01:31:38,283
You may have to.

1662
01:31:38,409 --> 01:31:40,452
Sam, just remember
the plan.
I know the plan.

1663
01:31:41,412 --> 01:31:43,915
Damn, it's premeditated.
It's...

1664
01:31:44,250 --> 01:31:47,585
It makes me an accomplice,
an accessory, an abettor.

1665
01:31:48,170 --> 01:31:49,964
It's also excessive force.

1666
01:31:50,340 --> 01:31:52,842
Sam,
the only thing excessive
we could do to Cady

1667
01:31:52,926 --> 01:31:55,845
would be to gut him
and eat his liver.

1668
01:31:55,929 --> 01:31:57,055
That might
be excessive.

1669
01:31:57,139 --> 01:31:59,391
Jesus Christ,
Kersek, I'm serious.

1670
01:31:59,475 --> 01:32:01,685
No, you're scared.

1671
01:32:02,228 --> 01:32:05,731
But that's okay.
I want you to
savor that fear.

1672
01:32:06,441 --> 01:32:08,651
You know,
the South evolved in fear.

1673
01:32:08,735 --> 01:32:12,948
Fear of the Indian,
fear of the slave,
fear of the damn Union.

1674
01:32:14,200 --> 01:32:17,286
The South has
a fine tradition
of savoring fear.

1675
01:32:26,381 --> 01:32:27,882
(INAUDIBLE)

1676
01:32:34,932 --> 01:32:36,600
SAM: What's the matter?

1677
01:32:37,143 --> 01:32:39,269
Don't look over!
Don't look.

1678
01:32:39,645 --> 01:32:41,606
(WHISPERING)
She's making me nervous.

1679
01:32:42,983 --> 01:32:44,567
What would
she normally do

1680
01:32:44,651 --> 01:32:46,402
if Sam wasn't around
to run her home?

1681
01:32:46,737 --> 01:32:48,155
She'd stay...
SAM: She'd stay over.

1682
01:32:48,990 --> 01:32:51,074
Well, then,
she stays over.

1683
01:33:38,838 --> 01:33:40,255
(TICKING)

1684
01:34:52,589 --> 01:34:54,214
(RATTLING)

1685
01:35:04,560 --> 01:35:05,811
(SNIFFLING)

1686
01:35:23,749 --> 01:35:24,791
Leigh?

1687
01:35:27,337 --> 01:35:28,837
What?
Leigh.

1688
01:35:29,339 --> 01:35:31,298
I know how
the dog died.

1689
01:35:32,425 --> 01:35:34,135
Sam, are you dreaming?
No. No.

1690
01:35:34,220 --> 01:35:35,637
I just had
the weirdest feeling

1691
01:35:35,721 --> 01:35:37,972
he was already
